Let's go over to the CSS,

00:04:00.075 --> 00:04:02.635
and we can reset these values.

00:04:02.635 --> 00:04:05.765
If we go just below the header and footer,

00:04:05.765 --> 00:04:08.045
let's tag at the UL.

00:04:08.045 --> 00:04:12.270
Then we could set the margin back to be zero.

00:04:12.680 --> 00:04:17.145
If we watch out for this when we refresh,

00:04:17.145 --> 00:04:21.770
we see everything move up as a default margin was removed.

00:04:21.770 --> 00:04:25.365
We can also do the same too to remove any default padding.

00:04:25.365 --> 00:04:28.225
Again, back over to the unordered list.

00:04:28.225 --> 00:04:31.565
Then we can reset the padding back to zero.

00:04:31.565 --> 00:04:35.029
If we keep a close eye out for me when we refresh,

00:04:35.029 --> 00:04:39.695
we see all the unordered lists are now moved over to the left hand side.

00:04:39.695 --> 00:04:43.790
This is something to bear in mind if you're wondering why something looks a little

00:04:43.790 --> 00:04:49.085
different than expected due to the browser adding some default values.

00:04:49.085 --> 00:04:52.595
Also, just to make things even more confusing,

00:04:52.595 --> 00:04:56.495
different browsers often have different values too.

